- No, my name's Leonard.

948
01:21:28,020 --> 01:21:30,420
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

949
01:21:30,660 --> 01:21:32,460
What's happened to Jimmy?

950
01:21:32,700 --> 01:21:36,100
- I don't know that, either. Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

951
01:21:36,340 --> 01:21:39,620
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done?

952
01:21:39,860 --> 01:21:43,100
I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

953
01:21:43,340 --> 01:21:47,500
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

954
01:21:49,140 --> 01:21:52,700
Your pocket?

955
01:22:14,540 --> 01:22:17,100
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

956
01:22:17,340 --> 01:22:19,820
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

957
01:22:20,060 --> 01:22:25,340
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

958
01:22:34,740 --> 01:22:37,980
Thank you.

959
01:22:52,700 --> 01:22:55,820
- On the house.
- Thanks.

960
01:22:59,420 --> 01:23:02,500
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

961
01:23:02,740 --> 01:23:06,140
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

962
01:23:06,380 --> 01:23:08,460
I guess it's poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

963
01:23:08,700 --> 01:23:13,140
You know the truth about my condition,
officer? You don't know anything.

964
01:23:13,380 --> 01:23:18,100
You feel angry, you don't know why.
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

965
01:23:18,340 --> 01:23:21,540
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea ten minutes later.

966
01:23:21,780 --> 01:23:24,500
Like Sammy.
What if I'd done something like Sammy?

967
01:23:24,740 --> 01:23:28,340
I didn't tell you?
What happened to Sammy and his wife?

968
01:23:28,580 --> 01:23:30,500
She came to see me at my office.

969
01:23:30,740 --> 01:23:35,300
<i>I didn't tell her what I really thought
but I never said that he was faking.</i>

970
01:23:35,540 --> 01:23:37,500
<i>Just that his condition was mental, 
not physical.</i>

971
01:23:37,740 --> 01:23:41,780
<i>I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.</i>

972
01:23:42,020 --> 01:23:46,260
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

973
01:24:00,100 --> 01:24:02,900
<i>She knew beyond a doubt
that he loved her,</i>

974
01:24:03,140 --> 01:24:07,260
<i>so she found a way to test him.</i>

975
01:24:17,220 --> 01:24:21,340
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

976
01:24:21,580 --> 01:24:25,060
Hm.

977
01:24:30,540 --> 01:24:33,980
<i>- She really thought she'd call his bluff. 
- There you go.</i>

978
01:24:34,220 --> 01:24:40,260
<i>Or she just didn't want to live with
the things she'd put him through.</i>

979
01:24:47,100 --> 01:24:49,980
Sammy?

980
01:24:50,540 --> 01:24:53,420
It's time for my shot.

981
01:24:57,820 --> 01:25:01,060
It won't hurt.

982
01:25:41,580 --> 01:25:44,580
<i>She went into a coma
and never recovered.</i>

983
01:25:44,820 --> 01:25:47,780
<i>Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.</i>

984
01:25:48,020 --> 01:25:49,820
Oh!

985
01:25:50,060 --> 01:25:54,180
He's been in a home ever since.
He doesn't even know his wife is dead.

986
01:25:54,420 --> 01:25:57,500
I was wrong about Sammy
and I was wrong about his wife.

987
01:25:57,740 --> 01:26:01,580
She wasn't interested in the money.
She needed to understand his problem.

988
01:26:01,820 --> 01:26:05,220
<i>His brain didn't respond to conditioning
but he wasn't a con man.</i>

989
01:26:05,460 --> 01:26:08,580
<i>And when she looked into his eyes, 
she thought he could be the same person.</i>

990
01:26:08,820 --> 01:26:10,660
<i>When I looked into his eyes, 
I thought I saw recognition.</i>

991
01:26:10,900 --> 01:26:12,700
Now I know you fake it.

992
01:26:12,940 --> 01:26:15,740
If you think you're supposed to recognise
somebody, you pretend to.

993
01:26:15,980 --> 01:26:19,260
<i>You bluff it to get a pat on the head
from the doctors.</i>

994
01:26:19,500 --> 01:26:23,980
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

995
01:26:24,100 --> 01:26:26,580
What drug dealer?

996
01:26:50,620 --> 01:26:53,460
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

997
01:26:53,700 --> 01:26:56,420
- It's OK, we know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

998
01:26:56,660 --> 01:26:58,420
The Jag's out front.

999
01:26:58,660 --> 01:27:01,380
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlours up north.

1000
01:27:01,620 --> 01:27:04,820
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1001
01:27:05,060 --> 01:27:06,780
- Give me the keys, I'll move it.
- It'll be all right.

1002
01:27:07,020 --> 01:27:08,820
- Wait out there.
- Oh, for Christ...

1003
01:27:09,060 --> 01:27:12,620
Give me a minute,
I've got to get something for you.

1004
01:27:15,540 --> 01:27:20,460
<i>Fact six. Car licence SG13 7IU.</i>

1005
01:27:25,020 --> 01:27:29,500
Look, wait a minute, will ya?

1006
01:27:30,540 --> 01:27:32,580
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1007
01:27:32,820 --> 01:27:35,500
Oh, man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1008
01:27:35,740 --> 01:27:37,940
- It's not safe for you to hang around.
- Why not?

1009
01:27:38,180 --> 01:27:41,220
Because that cop's looking for you.
I gotta get you a new identity...

1010
01:27:41,460 --> 01:27:44,540
...some new clothes, a different car
would do for now. Put these on.

1011
01:27:44,780 --> 01:27:46,420
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

1012
01:27:46,660 --> 01:27:50,420
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1013
01:27:50,660 --> 01:27:54,260
He's been calling you for days, slipping
envelopes under your door, shit like that.

1014
01:27:54,500 --> 01:27:58,180
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He's been laughing at you.

1015
01:27:58,420 --> 01:27:59,620
- You're full of shit.
- No, I'm not.

1016
01:27:59,860 --> 01:28:01,660
He knows you're no good on the phone
so he's been calling you up.

1017
01:28:01,900 --> 01:28:03,660
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

1018
01:28:03,900 --> 01:28:06,420
...so he slips shit under your door
to scare you into answering it...

1019
01:28:06,660 --> 01:28:11,460
...giving you a line of crap about John G
being a local drug dealer. Jimmy Grants.

1020
01:28:11,700 --> 01:28:14,220
- Who's Jimmy Grants?
- Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1021
01:28:14,460 --> 01:28:17,660
The cop wants to know how his operation
is run. He's got some score in mind.

1022
01:28:17,900 --> 01:28:20,180
- Somehow you're involved.
- How do you know him?

1023
01:28:20,420 --> 01:28:25,740
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1024
01:28:25,980 --> 01:28:28,060
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1025
01:28:28,300 --> 01:28:31,780
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1026
01:28:32,020 --> 01:28:35,340
Come on, Leonard, just go.

1027
01:28:53,300 --> 01:28:56,660
You "are" full of shit.

1028
01:28:57,860 --> 01:29:00,260
<i>Come by after. Natalie.</i>

1029
01:29:00,500 --> 01:29:03,860
<i>Ferdy's bar.</i>

1030
01:29:42,500 --> 01:29:46,140
Hey, Jimmy.

1031
01:29:46,140 --> 01:29:49,260
I'm sorry, I, uh,
thought you were somebody else.

1032
01:29:49,500 --> 01:29:51,100
Sorry.

1033
01:29:51,340 --> 01:29:54,820
That's OK.

1034
01:30:06,500 --> 01:30:10,500
This Jimmy Grants deals drugs
out of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1035
01:30:10,740 --> 01:30:14,140
But he's not going to bring her along?
He'll come by himself, right?

1036
01:30:14,380 --> 01:30:18,100
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1037
01:30:18,340 --> 01:30:21,460
No, officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1038
01:30:21,700 --> 01:30:25,500
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1039
01:30:25,740 --> 01:30:28,180
I'll be right there.

1040
01:31:08,020 --> 01:31:10,420
Lenny!

1041
01:31:11,060 --> 01:31:14,540
Officer Gammell?

1042
01:31:15,900 --> 01:31:19,380
Yeah. Come on.

1043
01:31:33,940 --> 01:31:37,340
- Hey, smile.
- Oh, don't, uh... Not here.

1044
01:31:37,580 --> 01:31:41,060
Over here.

1045
01:31:43,860 --> 01:31:46,260
Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?

1046
01:31:46,500 --> 01:31:49,220
You know what?
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1047
01:31:49,460 --> 01:31:53,500
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1048
01:31:54,580 --> 01:31:57,060
This is the directions, where he's going.

1049
01:31:57,300 --> 01:31:59,900
- My number's on the bottom if you...
- You're not coming?

1050
01:32:00,140 --> 01:32:04,340
Nah, it wouldn't be appropriate.

1051
01:32:06,620 --> 01:32:10,700
Nice picture. I look thin.

1052
01:32:11,820 --> 01:32:14,420
Hey, Lenny!

1053
01:32:14,660 --> 01:32:17,540
Make him beg.

1054
01:33:35,260 --> 01:33:38,740
Teddy!

1055
01:33:39,260 --> 01:33:41,900
Hey, Teddy!

1056
01:33:43,300 --> 01:33:46,580
Teddy!

1057
01:33:48,100 --> 01:33:50,060
Jimmy.

1058
01:33:50,300 --> 01:33:53,260
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1059
01:33:53,500 --> 01:33:55,260
Expecting any other Jimmys,
memory man?

1060
01:33:55,500 --> 01:33:59,420
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1061
01:33:59,660 --> 01:34:01,820
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1062
01:34:02,060 --> 01:34:04,620
Well?

1063
01:34:06,620 --> 01:34:08,300
Motherfuck!

1064
01:34:08,540 --> 01:34:10,860
What are you doing?

1065
01:34:11,420 --> 01:34:12,420
Strip.

1066
01:34:12,660 --> 01:34:16,540
- You're making a big fucking mistake!
- Strip!

1067
01:34:16,540 --> 01:34:19,340
My associates are not the kind of people
you wanna piss off.

1068
01:34:19,580 --> 01:34:21,020
Don't say anything else.

1069
01:34:21,260 --> 01:34:25,660
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1070
01:34:29,220 --> 01:34:31,100
Your pants, too.

1071
01:34:31,340 --> 01:34:33,540
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1072
01:34:33,780 --> 01:34:37,460
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1073
01:34:37,700 --> 01:34:41,340
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got two hundred grand in the car!

1074
01:34:41,580 --> 01:34:43,980
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1075
01:34:44,220 --> 01:34:46,300
- Just take the money and walk away.
- I don't want your fucking money.

1076
01:34:46,540 --> 01:34:48,700
Then, what?

1077
01:34:48,940 --> 01:34:53,620
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fucking life back!

1078
01:36:19,820 --> 01:36:22,500
Sammy.

1079
01:36:27,500 --> 01:36:29,380
<i>He said Sammy. 
How does he know about Sammy?</i>

1080
01:36:29,620 --> 01:36:33,100
Oh, fuck.

1081
01:36:50,620 --> 01:36:53,580
<i>What have I done?</i>

1082
01:36:53,820 --> 01:36:54,820
Hey, mister! I need help!

1083
01:36:55,060 --> 01:36:58,340
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.
We gotta get him to a doctor.

1084
01:36:58,580 --> 01:37:00,660
All right.

1085
01:37:00,900 --> 01:37:02,940
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1086
01:37:03,180 --> 01:37:05,860
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry, I'm a cop.

1087
01:37:06,100 --> 01:37:09,100
- Is he still breathing?
- Well, I don't know. Maybe.

1088
01:37:09,340 --> 01:37:13,980
- What the hell were you guys doing?
- I don't remember, I have this condition.

1089
01:37:14,220 --> 01:37:17,300
I hope it's not as serious as his
cos this guy's dead.

1090
01:37:17,540 --> 01:37:21,100
- Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!
- So you remember me now, huh?

1091
01:37:21,340 --> 01:37:25,620
- You "are" a fucking cop!
- And I'm the guy that helped you find him.

1092
01:37:25,860 --> 01:37:31,700
- Get up! Get up!
- Lenny, you got the wrong idea!

1093
01:37:32,940 --> 01:37:34,780
Who is that? He knew me.

1094
01:37:35,020 --> 01:37:37,420
Of course he did, he raped your wife,
he fucked up your brain.

1095
01:37:37,660 --> 01:37:39,460
Bullshit! He's not the guy.

1096
01:37:39,700 --> 01:37:43,260
His name is James F Grants. John G.
Check your tattoos.

1097
01:37:43,500 --> 01:37:47,620
- Why did he bring two hundred grand?
- What?

1098
01:37:48,020 --> 01:37:50,060
- What was it for?
- Amphetamines I told him I had.

1099
01:37:50,300 --> 01:37:53,580
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1100
01:37:53,820 --> 01:37:57,020
Look, Jimmy's your guy. I figured
we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1101
01:37:57,260 --> 01:37:59,860
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn.

1102
01:38:00,100 --> 01:38:04,140
He dealt out of there. The guy at the front
desk let him know if anybody came round.

1103
01:38:04,380 --> 01:38:06,420
He called Jimmy
the minute he saw you taking a picture.

1104
01:38:06,660 --> 01:38:08,820
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half.

1105
01:38:09,060 --> 01:38:11,300
He knew about Sammy,
why would I tell him about Sammy?!

1106
01:38:11,540 --> 01:38:14,620
You tell everybody about Sammy!
Everybody who'll listen!

1107
01:38:14,860 --> 01:38:16,740
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"

1108
01:38:16,980 --> 01:38:19,780
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1109
01:38:20,020 --> 01:38:23,620
So you lie to yourself to be happy.
There's nothing wrong with that.

1110
01:38:23,860 --> 01:38:28,660
We all do it. Who cares if there's a few
little details you'd rather not remember?

1111
01:38:28,900 --> 01:38:32,100
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

1112
01:38:32,340 --> 01:38:36,820
Your wife surviving the assault.
Her not believing your condition.

1113
01:38:37,060 --> 01:38:41,860
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1114
01:38:42,100 --> 01:38:44,340
The insulin.

1115
01:38:44,580 --> 01:38:47,020
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

1116
01:38:47,260 --> 01:38:49,980
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1117
01:38:50,220 --> 01:38:53,420
Condtitioning yourself to remember,
learning through repetition.

1118
01:38:53,660 --> 01:38:56,220
Sammy let his wife kill herself.
Sammy ended up in an institution.

1119
01:38:56,460 --> 01:38:59,460
Sammy was a con man. A faker.

1120
01:38:59,700 --> 01:39:01,620
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1121
01:39:01,860 --> 01:39:04,460
You exposed him for what he was.
A fraud.

1122
01:39:04,700 --> 01:39:07,540
I was wrong. That's the whole point.

1123
01:39:07,780 --> 01:39:12,420
- See, Sammy's wife came to me...
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1124
01:39:13,500 --> 01:39:17,780
It was your wife who had diabetes.

1125
01:39:21,900 --> 01:39:24,380
Ouch!

1126
01:39:24,900 --> 01:39:27,460
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1127
01:39:27,700 --> 01:39:31,180
You sure?

1128
01:39:33,900 --> 01:39:35,620
Ouch! Cut it out!

1129
01:39:35,860 --> 01:39:37,660
She wasn't diabetic.

1130
01:39:37,900 --> 01:39:41,340
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1131
01:39:41,580 --> 01:39:44,340
I guess I can only make you remember
the things you want to be true.

1132
01:39:44,580 --> 01:39:47,060
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1133
01:39:47,300 --> 01:39:49,220
He was to you.

1134
01:39:49,460 --> 01:39:52,540
Come on, you got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

1135
01:39:52,780 --> 01:39:55,060
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

1136
01:39:55,300 --> 01:39:57,180
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

1137
01:39:57,420 --> 01:39:58,980
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

1138
01:39:59,220 --> 01:40:01,380
- Somehow I'll know.
- You won't remember!

1139
01:40:01,620 --> 01:40:02,860
When it's done, I will know.

1140
01:40:03,100 --> 01:40:07,580
I thought so, too, I was sure of it,
but you didn't!

1141
01:40:09,580 --> 01:40:14,180
That's right. The real John G.
I helped you find him over a year ago.

1142
01:40:14,420 --> 01:40:17,020
- He's already dead.
- Don't lie to me any more.

1143
01:40:17,260 --> 01:40:19,100
Look, Lenny...

1144
01:40:19,340 --> 01:40:22,260
...I was the cop assigned
to your wife's case, I believed you.

1145
01:40:22,500 --> 01:40:24,740
I thought you deserved
a chance for revenge.

1146
01:40:24,980 --> 01:40:28,060
I'm the one that helped you find
the other guy in your bathroom that night.

1147
01:40:28,300 --> 01:40:30,300
The guy that cracked your skull
and fucked your wife.

1148
01:40:30,540 --> 01:40:34,380
We found him, you killed him.

1149
01:40:34,500 --> 01:40:36,620
But you didn't remember.

1150
01:40:36,860 --> 01:40:41,660
So I helped you start looking again,
looking for the guy you already killed.

1151
01:40:41,900 --> 01:40:46,260
- Oh, yeah? So who was he?
- Just some guy. Does it matter who?

1152
01:40:46,500 --> 01:40:50,900
No reason, Lenny, no conspiracy,
just bad fucking luck.

1153
01:40:51,140 --> 01:40:56,020
Couple of junkies too strung out
to realise your wife didn't live alone.

1154
01:40:56,220 --> 01:41:00,660
But when you killed him
I was so convinced that you'd remember.

1155
01:41:00,900 --> 01:41:03,140
But it didn't stick.

1156
01:41:03,380 --> 01:41:07,020
Like nothing ever sticks,
like this won't stick.

1157
01:41:09,580 --> 01:41:11,540
I took that picture.

1158
01:41:11,780 --> 01:41:15,260
Just when you did it.

1159
01:41:16,380 --> 01:41:21,020
Look how happy you are.
I wanted to see that face again.

1160
01:41:21,260 --> 01:41:23,500
- Oh, gee, thanks(!)
- Fuck you.

1161
01:41:23,740 --> 01:41:27,460
I gave you a reason to live
and you were more than happy to help.

1162
01:41:27,700 --> 01:41:33,700
You don't want the truth. You make up
your own truth, like your police file.

1163
01:41:33,940 --> 01:41:36,740
It was complete when I gave it to you.
Who took out the twelve pages?

1164
01:41:36,980 --> 01:41:38,140
You, probably.

1165
01:41:38,380 --> 01:41:40,540
- No, it wasn't me, see, it was you.
- Why would I do that?

1166
01:41:40,780 --> 01:41:43,340
To create a puzzle you could never solve.

1167
01:41:43,580 --> 01:41:45,340
Do you know how many towns...

1168
01:41:45,580 --> 01:41:49,460
...how many John Gs or James Gs?
I mean, shit, Lenny, I'm a fucking John G.

1169
01:41:49,700 --> 01:41:52,620
- Your name's Teddy.
- My mother calls me Teddy.

1170
01:41:52,860 --> 01:41:54,660
